CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 23, 1961, pg. 21, reads: "Birthday Celebration - A birthday dinner party was given for little Miss Gina Jenkins, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. James E. Jenkins of 7834 Zinga [Tioga?] St., who was three years old on September 18. Her guests, left to right, were: Belinda Chatman, Bunny Chatman, Richard Spann, Gina Jenkins, George Eddie Smith, and Darlene Harris. Among her gifts were money, clothes and toys. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Belinda Chatman, Bunny Chatman, Richard Spann, Gina Jenkins, George Eddie Smith and Darlene Harris gathered behind table with birthday cake and paper plates, for third birthday party of Gina Jenkins in her home
